    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="280"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/761</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Russian Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_US1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ughet</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PFL">Polk</persName>
                    </hi>: Referring to my letter of March 14th,<note n="64" xml:id="d280fn64">Not
                        found in the Department files.</note> with which I transmitted to you the
                    Ambassador’s views relative to your note of February 28th,<note n="65"
                        xml:id="d280fn65">Not printed.</note> I have the honor to inform you that I
                    am at present in receipt of a cable from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Omsk,
                    stating that on March 14th an agreement<note n="66" xml:id="d280fn66">Apparently
                        refers to statement of Mar. 14; see <ref target="#pg_257">p.
                        257</ref>.</note> had been concluded concerning the Inter-Allied supervision
                    of Railways and expressing its complete satisfaction with the results achieved,
                    and especially emphasising its satisfaction that the Allied supervision bears
                    the character of technical aid and cooperation with the Russian Railway
                    personnel and that it in no way infringes upon any of the sovereign rights of
                    the Russian people.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_US1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ughet</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
